[h1]Your First C# Program[/h1]

Visual Studio will automatically generate some code for your project: [code format="cs" ]using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using System.Linq;
using System.Text;
using System.Threading.Tasks;
 
namespace SoloLearn
{
   class Program
   {
      static void [b]Main[/b](string[] args)
      {
      }
   }
}[/code]
You will learn what each of the statements do in the upcoming lessons. 
For now, remember that every C# console application must contain a [b]method (a function) named Main[/b]. Main is the starting point of every application, i.e. the point where our program starts execution from.
[note]We will learn about classes, methods, arguments, and namespaces in the upcoming lessons.[/note]
